Package com.piggybox.http

User Defined Functions for processing HTTP data logs.

See:
          Description

Class Summary
AppCategoryClassify Given a user agent (only mobile currently), classify the application as 'video', 'music', 'social', 'im' and so on.
ExtractUrlHost Extract the host name from given URL string.
ExtractUrlParams Extract parameters in URL and return a map of pairs.
MobileType Given a mobile user agent string, detect and return a device/OS name.
ServiceCategoryClassify Given a host string, this function return the host category as long as the class information.
StripUrl  
StripUrlLeft Strip the protocol prefix in URL address and return the left part.
StripUrlRight Strip parameters in a URL address.
TopPrivateDomain Get the top-level domain from URL.
UrlFromHostUri Concatenate Host and Uri fileds in HTTP header into a URL address.
UserAgentClassify Given a user agent string, this UDF classifies clients to 'mobile' and 'desktop'.
